They've kind of been possible for a long time, but now that it's kind of gotten first class

07:17.080 --> 07:18.980
support.

07:18.980 --> 07:22.080
Why do you care about this?

07:22.080 --> 07:27.440
I'm not going to encourage you to write directly web components yourself if you're using React.

07:27.440 --> 07:29.040
Just use React.

07:29.040 --> 07:31.240
Why this is actually interesting is for library authors.

07:31.240 --> 07:36.480
For an example, I was talking to an auth company, dscope, if you've heard of them, it's a perfectly

